  "description": [
    "Snavalog THE NAVYS OLDEST NEWSPAPER Vol 59 No 5 First Naval District Will Authorize Funds For 011Dutv Sludv V Naval personnel on active duty who enroll in courses of instruc tion may receive up to 75 of the tuition cost from First Naval District funds Under this pro gram funds are available for tuition aid not to exceed 7 50 per semester hour or 5 00 per quarter hour for a maximum of six semester hours in one se mester or 6 quarter hours per quarter An applicant must be accepted by the educational institution be fore the request is sent to COM ONE for allocation of funds but requests should be submitted pri or to enrollment and far enough in advance to determine avail ability of funds i If funds are not available at the time resubmis sion may be requested at a later datei If approval is granted the Commandant will notify the in stitution the student and his commanding officer BUPERS Instruction 156018 and COMONE Notice 1560 of 15 January 1959 contain the details and format for applying Those interested can get information on this Tuition Aid Program from the IE Office War College Fool lighters Announce"
